<item>
            <title>[HIVE-188] hive CLI should quit when stdout is closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-188</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;bin/hive -e &apos;select * from a_big_table;&apos; | head&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The process does not end after printing out the first 10 lines.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is probably because System.out.println is not checking errors. We need to manually call boolean System.out.checkError() to know if the output is closed or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
